Indexing check (frontend pages only):

- Confirm this is a user-facing frontend route/page (otherwise ignore SEO rules).
- Crawlability gate (blocking):
  - If we can't reliably serve meaningful HTML + correct metadata to crawlers (SSR/prerender), default to `noindex` until fixed (even for Creator/Vault).
- Decide indexability:
  - Creator + Vault pages: indexable by default if they provide unique user-visible value.
  - Sort/filter/pagination variants: `noindex` + canonical to the hub URL.
  - Ambiguous/thin/duplicate pages: default to `noindex`.
- Canonical:
  - Exactly one canonical URL per entity.
  - Paginated pages canonicalize to the hub.
- Metadata:
  - Unique title/description per URL.
  - Robots (`index,follow` vs `noindex,follow`) must match the indexability decision.
  - OG + Twitter tags required for indexable pages.
- Performance:
  - Call out any LCP/CLS/TTFB regressions (performance is an SEO feature).

